public interface IndexedVisitable<Type>

Applies a visitor to a subset of the objects in an indexed container.

Convenience object to allow applying an IndexedVisitable.IndexedVisitor callback over some subset of the elements of a container.

Visitors can not mofify the value or object reference stored in the container.

The value returned by a Visitor is used to signal early stops of the traversal, and is aggregated into a final result available to the application.

See Also:
Iterator, Iterable.iterator(), Indexable, Indexable.indexes(), IndexedOperable

Nested Class Summary
static interface IndexedVisitable.IndexedVisitor<Type,Par>
          A callback, or procedure, used by the visit(net.varkhan.base.containers.IndexedVisitable.IndexedVisitor, Par).

An IndexedVisitor callback takes an index and single object of the type supported by the container, processes that element, and returns a long value that signifies the end of the iteration if negative, and is added to the total visiting count otherwise.
